<p><strong>Guidance:</strong></p>
<p>
  Member state should provide information on the objectives of the coordination
  between MSFD and other policies such as European Green Deal (EGD),
  Biodiversity Strategy (BDS), Zero Pollution Action plan (ZPA), Fit for 55
  packages are presented. The mechanisms set for the coordination between the
  MSFD and other policies such as EGD, BDS, ZPA, Fit for 55 are described.
</p>
<p>The assessor should very if:</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p>
      The information provided understandable and clearly making references to
      specific standards/practices/norms that it links to under other types of
      instruments?
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      The information provided is understandable and clearly making references
      to &ldquo;governance mechanisms&rdquo; that are established?
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  For the response option, the assessors should select: &ldquo;Yes&rdquo; if the
  mechanisms and outcomes of coordination with all the mentioned policies are
  clearly presented, &ldquo;Partially&rdquo; if the mechanisms and outcomes of
  coordination with some of the mentioned policies are clearly presented, and
  &ldquo;No&rdquo; if the mechanisms and outcomes of coordination with the
  mentioned policies are not presented. If other policies are presented, the
  assessors should specify the policies in the summary box and describe the
  mechanisms and outcomes of coordination.
</p>
